This Canticum falls into three divi- sions (for metrical analysis see critical note) t-(A) 313-319, Solo of Callidamates: (B) 319-335, Duet of Delphium and Callidamates; this is a very effective passage, fnll of life and humour: (C) 336-347, Quartette of the above with Philolaches and Philematium. Altogether this scene must be regarded as one of the most vigorous in Plautus.
